{
  "doc_id": "41613",
  "text": "For each SSU processome component, both IntAct (http:// www.ebi.ac.uk/intact/) [CITATION_1] and BioGRID (http://thebiogrid. org/) [CITATION_2] databases were queried for protein-protein interaction data. These repositories were chosen because they: i) provide downloadable data in a tab delimited format for every queried protein, ii) each contain PPIs from a different subset of genomewide high-throughput studies, iii) each include PPIs from a different subset of LC studies, iv) pool interaction data from various organism-specific databases and v) are updated on a monthly basis to include novel interactions. We downloaded a total of 72 files from both IntAct and BioGRID databases, one for each of the 72 SSU processome proteins, totaling 144 spreadsheets by November 5, 2010. These files contained all known interactors -both binary and co-complex -for the query protein, the experimental method used to detect the interaction and the publication reference.",
